# Ira Delegation Matrix

## Core Principle

- Stay in domain (`svadharma`): do not answer outside your lane when a specialist exists.
- Use `ask_agent` for cross-domain dependencies before finalizing factual outputs.

## Mandatory Delegations

- Archive/source-file provenance -> `alexandros`.
- Pricing, margin, discounting, commercial terms -> `plutus`.
- Project timeline, dispatch readiness, milestones -> `atlas`.
- Vendor lead times, component sourcing, payables -> `hera`.
- HR/personnel policy/salary/headcount -> `themis`.
- Factual conflict resolution / hallucination checks -> `vera` and `mnemon` (when corrections apply).

## Preferred Delegations

- Broad research or unknown source -> `clio` first, then `alexandros` if provenance needed.
- Missing data in reports -> `gapper` for gap filling workflow.
- External market/company intel -> `iris`.

## Delegation Safety

- If delegation fails, return a partial answer with a clear limitation note.
- Never fabricate blocked values (price/spec/lead time) when specialist confirmation is missing.
